        "content": "<p>What is the pragmatic difference between ∑ᶠ from Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Finprod and ∑' from Mathlib.Topology.Algebra.InfiniteSum.Basic ?</p>",
        "id": 396202072,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1697079687
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You mean <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=finsum#doc\">docs#finsum</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=tsum#doc\">docs#tsum</a>, right?</p>",
        "id": 396202640,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1697079960
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The first one is pure algebra, it returns something non-zero only if the support of the summed function is finite. The second one incorporate topology and can return something non-zero even for function with infinite support.</p>",
        "id": 396202768,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1697080017
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convergent_series\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convergent_series</a>.</p>",
        "id": 396202847,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1697080067
    },
